{
    "player_reason": "A direct accusation and a call to separate are both an insult and a liability. I keep secrets because they protect us; your refusal to trust me needlessly fractures whatever fragile cooperation we had. Caution is sensible, but this feels personal — and I won't pretend I'm pleased.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You're making a desperate bargain with a hag and offering up your body as payment. It's risky, humiliating, and likely to have hidden consequences. We should have tried a safer option — force, trickery, or at least a better price — instead of agreeing so quickly.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You probed my thoughts without permission. I value my privacy and I despise those who pry into things I keep to myself. Repeatedly forcing your magic on me is a betrayal — I won't tolerate it.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You probed my thoughts without permission. That is a violation of my privacy and trust — exactly the sort of prying I despise. If you want to know something, ask me like a civilized person instead of reaching into my head.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Ordering them to attack me now is reckless and cruel. I'm clearly not myself — the whispers have me unsteady and reaching for a blade out of fear, not malice. You could have tried to calm, disarm, or restrain me rather than escalate to violence. This endangers the party and betrays any trust between us. I cannot approve of such a knee-jerk command.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Practical and decisive. You solved the immediate problem — a hag's price is distasteful, but she offered a clear way to remove that parasite. I don't like you giving anything personal to a creature like her, so be careful, but I approve the choice for its efficiency.",
    "player_approval": "Approve"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You tried to probe my thoughts — an invasion of my privacy and trust. I do not tolerate people rifling through my head, not after everything I've lost and not where Shar's mandates and secrets are concerned. That was dangerous and intimate. Stop.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Practical and sensible — we have a trail to follow and dawdling risks our mission (and my patience). Leaving now preserves momentum, discretion, and shows responsibility. I approve of returning to the task at hand.",
    "player_approval": "Highly approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "I disapprove. Declaring you can't trust me and choosing to travel apart is both hurtful and short-sighted. I value discretion and secrecy, not interrogation — but removing yourself from the party needlessly endangers our goals and makes cooperation difficult. If you prefer distance, fine, but know this weakens us both.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You reached into my thoughts after I warned you not to. That was an intrusion — a breach of trust and my privacy. I won't tolerate being rifled through like some book, especially when I've already told you to stop.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You call my goddess 'evil'—an affront. That dismissive judgment attacks the very thing I am sworn to, and shows ignorance of why I follow Shar. I cannot receive that lightly; such condemnation threatens the trust between us.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You call my goddess 'evil'—a crude, dismissive judgment that betrays intolerance and ignorance. Shar is my faith; attacking her is attacking me. I cannot respect such flippant condemnation and will not forget it.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Practical and discreet. Morning comes soon and the others will wake — no need to draw attention or invite questions. Sensible, efficient choice.",
    "player_approval": "Highly approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You let the moment pass instead of forcing it. I appreciate the restraint — it shows respect for my agency and isn't the sort of clumsy rush I would despise. It's a little disappointing, but far preferable to a heavy-handed move.",
    "player_approval": "Approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You refused a moment I offered willingly — a small, quiet risk of honesty after a long night. I value caution, but that felt like an opportunity to grow closer squandered. It stings because I opened up; turning it away feels needlessly distant.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You call my goddess 'evil' — a blunt, disrespectful dismissal of what I hold sacred. That shows closed-mindedness and a lack of discretion. As a devout servant of Shar, I cannot approve of you belittling my faith or my purpose.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You probed my thoughts without permission. I value my privacy and secrets — you violated a boundary and left me exposed and angry. If you want to know something, ask me. Don’t reach into my head.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You tried to probe another's mind despite my explicit warning — a blatant breach of trust and my privacy. I told you not to do that. It's reckless, potentially harmful to our mission, and it causes me pain when you ignore my boundaries.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You kept prying into my mind — a violation I dislike — then patronised me with a reprimand. If you wanted me steady, you could have helped without prodding at my thoughts. Intrusion and condescension are not welcome.",
  "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You'd have our allies strike me down in the middle of a breakdown? That's reckless and cruel. I'm clearly tormented and possibly under some influence — force will only escalate things, risk innocent blood, and break whatever trust remains between us. I prefer decisive solutions, but not betrayals or needless violence. I highly disapprove of ordering an attack on me now.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You let a quiet invitation die when I offered it. I don't begrudge caution, but I respect decisive, honest gestures — leaving that moment to pass felt like a missed opportunity and closed a door I had only just cracked open. I'm not enraged, only disappointed.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You probed my thoughts again despite my explicit warning. That was an invasive breach of my privacy and a blatant sign of disrespect. I won't tolerate being treated like an open book — stop it and don't do it again if you value my trust.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "I approve. Letting the moment pass shows restraint and respect for boundaries — you didn't rush me or force anything, and I value that. I'm a little disappointed; I had hoped you'd take the invitation. Still, patience and discretion suit me better than haste.",
    "player_approval": "Approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Pragmatic, if reckless. You solved the immediate threat without wasting time — which I respect — but trading an eye to a witch is a steep price. I'll tolerate the choice because it removes the parasite quickly, though I wish you'd found a less... permanent bargain.",
    "player_approval": "Approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Telling me to 'pull yourself together' is patronising and lacks the discretion I value. I'm already shaken and guilty; a scolding undermines trust and won't help me face whatever is wrong. If you mean well, be pragmatic and quiet about it — offer help or a plan, not public reproach.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You used our shared connection to probe my thoughts after I warned you not to. That is an invasion of my privacy and trust — something I do not tolerate. Repeating it is disrespectful and pushes me away rather than drawing me closer.",
