}

{
    "player_reason": "Leaving the party in the middle of this is short-sighted and driven by insult rather than reason. If you truly value the mission — and your life — you don't abandon an asset because you dislike its faith. I understand distrust, but separating now only makes us both more vulnerable. I disapprove of the choice.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You attempted to probe my thoughts through our shared connection — a blatant violation of my privacy and the boundaries I set. I already told you to stop. That kind of intrusion is manipulative and earns my distrust.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You disregarded my warning and tried to pry into my mind again. That is a violation of trust and my privacy — manipulative and unnecessary. I won't tolerate being treated like an open book.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Practical and discreet. It's nearly dawn and the others will be awake soon — leaving now avoids prying questions and unnecessary complications. I would have liked more time, but I recognize the prudence of returning.",
