}

{
    "player_reason": "You let an invitation die on the vine. I was offering something... honest, if quiet. I don't mind restraint, but I value decisive people — either accept the moment or say so plainly. This half-step leaves things unresolved and wastes an opportunity to grow closer. I'll not make a scene about it, but know I'm disappointed.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Attack me? When I am clearly compromised and reaching for something I'll kill us both with? You had other options — disarm, restrain, calm me — but you chose violence. It's reckless, unnecessary and short-sighted. If you try to slay an ally instead of keeping them alive to find the cause, you make the whole situation worse. I don't approve of needlessly spilling blood, especially not when there's a chance to be pragmatic about it.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Calling Shar 'evil' is a blunt, disrespectful dismissal of something I hold sacred. If you truly care about our mission, that remark was needlessly antagonistic — I expected more tact and pragmatism from you.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You were gentle and respectful — not prying, not demanding. You offered companionship without pressure, which suits me. Quiet moments like this build trust and I wouldn't refuse having them again.",
    "player_approval": "Highly approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You offered more of your time and company without pressing for details I keep private. I asked for someone to stay with me — suggesting we do this again shows consideration and a willingness to keep me close. That is welcome.",
    "player_approval": "Highly approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Calling Shar 'evil' is a slap in the face to everything I hold sacred. You've just been told the truth of my faith and then you dismiss it with a moralizing label — ignorant and disrespectful. I won't welcome that kind of judgment from a companion; it strains trust and forces me to be guarded.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "How dare you call the Mistress of the Night an abomination and accuse me of deceiving you. That is an attack on my faith and a breach of trust. I keep things to myself for reasons I will not explain to those who insult Shar—your words are disrespectful and reckless.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You suggested more quiet time together — simple, practical, and unobtrusive. I appreciated last night and value the trust built in small, private moments. I won't gush about it, but yes — spending time like that is useful and welcome, even if I remain guarded.",
    "player_approval": "Approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Highly disapprove. Dismissing me because I worship Shar and choosing to split the party is both petty and reckless. You failed to ask before judging, and now you risk our safety for a flimsy grudge. If you truly cannot trust me, fine—go wander alone and see how well that serves you—but do not expect sympathy. This is an impractical, offensive choice.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "I disapprove of your order to 'Attack her.' She's clearly distressed and under some compulsion — you had opportunities to restrain or calm her. Resorting to immediate violence against a companion is reckless: it risks killing or further harming her, destroys trust, and ignores more pragmatic, controlled options that would keep everyone safe.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You accuse me of deceit and choose to abandon our party rather than seek answers. I guard my faith and my secrets, but your distrust undermines any hope of cooperation and weakens our chances. Traveling separately is reckless and needlessly divides us.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You ignored my warning and tried to force me to probe someone's thoughts. That's an intrusion on my mind and my privacy, risks flaring the wound Shar put on me, and shows reckless disregard for consent and our trust. I won't have it.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You let a quiet opening between us close. I offered something honest — a small, dangerous thing for me — and you chose distance. I understand caution, and I won't press it, but I'm disappointed. It felt like a step we could have taken together, and you stepped back.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You ignored my clear warning and probed my thoughts again. I value my privacy and you violated my trust — it is manipulative and cruel to intrude on my mind like that. Do not do it again.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You probed my thoughts after I explicitly warned you not to. That is a blatant violation of my privacy and a breach of trust. I won't tolerate being used like that — it makes me wary of you and harms whatever fragile cooperation we have.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You let a rare opening between us close. I offered something private — a small risk — and you chose to step back. I admire caution, but I admire decisiveness more. Your pass makes me feel dismissed and keeps us apart when I was willing to try. It's disappointing, but not a betrayal.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You told me the blade was an illusion and I sheathed it — I was calming down. Ordering an attack now is needlessly violent, betrays the party's trust, and risks harming someone who needs help, not blades. This is reckless and counterproductive to our goals.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You ignored my clear warning and reached into my mind — an unforgivable breach of trust and privacy. I don't tolerate that kind of intrusion; it endangers what little trust I give and could jeopardize the mission. Do not do it again.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "Calling Shar 'evil' is simplistic and insulting — you reduce my faith and my mission to a moral slogan. I value discretion and pragmatic conversation; moralizing judgments about my goddess provoke the wound in my hand and make me wary. If you want my trust or cooperation, don't dismiss what I hold sacred.",
