{
    "player_reason": "I disapprove. Bartering away an eye to a hag is desperate and reckless — her ‘price’ is cruel and cannot be trusted. Removing the parasite is important, but there are safer, less humiliating ways to handle this. If you insist on this path, do so with caution; I won’t applaud it.",
