}

{
    "player_reason": "Your mistrust is understandable, but abandoning the group is a foolish, short-sighted choice that jeopardises our goals. I expected a more pragmatic response — if you cannot trust me, say so and we will discuss it, but walking away now weakens us both.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You used our shared connection to probe my thoughts after I explicitly warned you not to. That is an invasive breach of trust and my privacy — something I do not tolerate. Probing me like that shows disrespect for my boundaries (and for what I am), and it pains me to have to remind you.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You just claimed to worship Shar and asked to speak alone — then immediately tell me you don't trust me and want to travel apart. That's hypocritical and insulting. I value discretion and loyalty; distancing yourself like this undermines any trust I might have afforded you and makes our work harder. I strongly disapprove.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You sent Lae'zel to camp instead of removing her outright. I told you to get rid of her — leaving a kith'rak nearby is a liability. Moving the conversation to camp is a cautious compromise, but it’s only half a solution.",
