{
    "player_reason": "You order an ally to attack me while I'm already fractured and pleading — that's a betrayal, not a solution. The whispering has me on edge; I needed help or restraint, not assassination. Your command is needlessly violent and destroys trust. If you wanted me stopped, there were less cruel, more pragmatic options than turning the party against me.",
